newsitem.title: USA: CBOT October soymeal, soyoil contracts end quietly.
newsitem.headline: CBOT October soymeal, soyoil contracts end quietly.

text.p: CBOT October soymeal and soyoil futures contracts expired without incident at 1201 CDT Tuesday with Cargill said to be a late soymeal buyer, traders said.
"It was a pretty quiet close," a floor trader said. "Cargill bought and that really turned the market around."
Soymeal futures jumped to $235.50 early as commercials and funds got out of short positions but traders said activity was generally quiet.
Soymeal closed at $231.00 per ton, up $1.30 from the previous day. Soyoil ended at 22.75 cent a lb, down 0.16 from Monday's close.
